rComments: Professor Farish gives good feedback, however, he's a tough grader so does the TA.
Cares a lot about the content and students. Fun and engaging lectures that challenge you to learn. Overall a great experience and professor

Although the lecture is a OK, but the grading is terrible! Mister Farish doesn't seem like a professor who cares. He is sarcastic and unfriendly. The TA is awful. She can't even speak proper English and answers without understanding the question. Overall, I won't recommend this course to anyone! There's better course and Prof out there folks!

He's the best! Super interesting lecture (even for those which he claimed to be "dry" he managed to make them engaging) and decent assignment grading. Attendance is a must and I mean why on earth would you miss his class?

Prof Farish is an amazing lecturer. His lectures were incredible thorough and informative. He is incredible organized, very approachable, and super helpful. He gives good feedback on assignments and is accessible outside of class.

Prof Farish was one of my favourite profs in all my 4 years of uni. He is very organized, posts slides a day before class, his lectures were very easy to follow, he is approachable and understanding. He is very intellectual and passionate about geography and explains his ideas very well in lectures. I wish I'd known about him sooner

Visit and talk to him in office hours, he is very helpful and listens to students. Reading selection was very good, mix of theory, case studies and contemporary readings. Good usage of visuals, photographs in lecture slides, helpful for visual learners.

Professor Farish is an approachable and helpful professor who is very well-versed in the course material. His assignments may sometimes seem daunting, but he is always there to help and to give advice on how to best approach the project. Many students miss the main point of his course, but paying attention and putting in the effort really pays off.
Good prof. Got alot of help.

He is neither arrogant nor boring as previous comments suggest. He is serious and to gain full worth from his (extensive) knowledge you have to listen carefully. There is nothing wrong with that. Also he is more committed and helpful than any other professor I've had, devoting tons of time to office hours and providing detailed feedback.
the best!

I agree with the below poster. Assignments were extremely easy, it was the TA's that challenged this notion. Very nit-picky marking, and one can tell the TA's have been told to curve down to the extreme. He was not helpful at all, when going for help. Very tough semester.

As a student in Geography, I look forward to all my GGR courses. I felt that this course was all over the place. Farish uses multiple 'case studies' as he likes to call them to make his point. Readings are somewhat useless. Lectures contain A LOT of information. Expectations for assignments are clearly stated, however they are unfairly graded.
Wow. What a disastrous course. The guy is highly condescending as well, not a good way to end the day.
I dont know why my previous comment was deleted, so, I'll write the same again. Dropped the course two weeks in. Needs to learn how to lecture. Seems angry all the time, no pleasant going to class.
Not good.

He was Terrible, the TA was terrible (both were buddy, buddy). Really arrogant guy, and gets irritated easily if one doesn't understand a concept. Asked a question more than once, and was shot down. But, did very well in the course because I was interested in the material. Liked the course material, hated him.
Very Interesting.  Obviously Enjoys Urban Geography. Very Enthusiastic.
wonderful
No Comments
